{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Warnings against Foolishness"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, if you have put up security for your neighbor, if you have struck hands in pledge with a stranger,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "if you have been trapped by the words of your lips, ensnared by the words of your mouth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "then do this, my son, to free yourself, for you have fallen into your neighbor’s hands: Go, humble yourself,[^22] and press your plea with your neighbor."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Allow no sleep to your eyesor slumber to your eyelids."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Free yourself, like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter,[^23] like a bird from the snare of the fowler."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Walk in the manner of the ant, O slacker; observe its ways and become wise."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Without a commander, without an overseer or ruler,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "it prepares its provisions in summer; it gathers its food at harvest."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "How long will you lie there, O slacker? When will you get up from your sleep?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to rest,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and poverty will come upon you like a robber, and need like a bandit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A worthless person, a wicked man, walks with a perverse mouth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "winking his eyes, speaking with his feet, and pointing with his fingers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "With deceit in his heart he devises evil; he continually sows discord."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore calamity will come upon him suddenly; in an instant he will be shattered beyond recovery."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "There are six things that the LORD hates, seven that are detestable to Him:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "haughty eyes,\na lying tongue,\nhands that shed innocent blood,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "a heart that devises wicked schemes,\nfeet that run swiftly to evil,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "a false witness who gives false testimony,\nand one who stirs up discord among brothers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Warnings against Adultery"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "law",
          "text": "My son, keep your father’s commandment, and do not forsake your mother’s teaching."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Bind them always upon your heart; tie them around your neck."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When you walk, they will guide you; when you lie down, they will watch over you;\nwhen you awake, they will speak to you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "law",
          "text": "For this commandment is a lamp, this teaching is a light, and the reproofs of discipline are the way to life,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to keep you from the evil woman, from the smooth tongue of the adulteress.[^24]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not lust in your heart for her beautyor let her captivate you with her eyes.[^25]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the levy of the prostitute is poverty,[^26] and the adulteress preys upon your very life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can a man embrace fire and his clothes not be burned?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can a man walk on hot coalswithout scorching his feet?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So is he who sleeps with another man’s wife; no one who touches her will go unpunished."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Men do not despise the thiefif he steals to satisfy his hunger."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yet if caught, he must pay sevenfold; he must give up all the wealth of his house."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who commits adultery lacks judgment; whoever does so destroys himself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Wounds and dishonor will befall him, and his reproach will never be wiped away."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For jealousy enrages a husband, and he will show no mercy in the day of vengeance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He will not be appeased by any ransom, or persuaded by lavish gifts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}